  "text": "## CronJob API v1beta1 to batch/v1 Migration in Kubernetes\n\n### Overview\nKubernetes migrated CronJob from the deprecated batch/v1beta1 API to the stable batch/v1 API. The v1beta1 version was marked as deprecated in v1.21 and removed in v1.25. Both versions support the TimeZone field for specifying the time zone for job execution.\n\n### Type Definitions\n\n**External API Types:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/types.go` (lines 678-760): Defines CronJob, CronJobList, and CronJobSpec for batch/v1, including the TimeZone field at line 732 as `*string`\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/types.go` (lines 42-140): Defines CronJob, CronJobList, and CronJobSpec for batch/v1beta1, including the TimeZone field at line 101 as `*string`\n\n**Internal API Type:**\n- `pkg/apis/batch/types.go` (lines 636-720): Defines the internal batch.CronJob and batch.CronJobSpec used for conversion between versions, including TimeZone field at line 686\n\n### Conversion Functions\n\nThe conversion between v1beta1 and batch/v1 is handled through the internal batch API representation:\n\n**v1beta1 ↔ Internal Conversion (pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/zz_generated.conversion.go):**\n- `Convert_v1beta1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob` (line 109): Public wrapper\n- `autoConvert_v1beta1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob` (line 97): Implementation - copies ObjectMeta, calls spec and status converters\n- `Convert_v1beta1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec` (line 186): Public wrapper\n- `autoConvert_v1beta1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec` (line 171): Implementation - converts Schedule, TimeZone (line 173), StartingDeadlineSeconds, ConcurrencyPolicy, Suspend, JobTemplate, and history limits\n- `Convert_batch_CronJob_To_v1beta1_CronJob` (line 125): Reverse conversion\n- `Convert_batch_CronJobSpec_To_v1beta1_CronJobSpec` (line 205): Reverse spec conversion\n\n**v1 ↔ Internal Conversion (pkg/apis/batch/v1/zz_generated.conversion.go):**\n- `Convert_v1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob` (line 230): Public wrapper\n- `autoConvert_v1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob`: Implementation\n- `Convert_v1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec` (line 307): Public wrapper\n- `autoConvert_v1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec` (line 292): Implementation - identical to v1beta1 conversion, handling TimeZone at line 294\n- `Convert_batch_CronJob_To_v1_CronJob` (line 246): Reverse conversion\n- `Convert_batch_CronJobSpec_To_v1_CronJobSpec` (line 326): Reverse spec conversion\n\n### TimeZone Field Addition\n\nThe TimeZone field (`*string`) is present in both v1beta1 and v1 versions:\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/types.go:101`: TimeZone with comprehensive documentation on time zone validation\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/types.go:732`: TimeZone field with identical documentation\n- `pkg/apis/batch/types.go:686`: Internal representation\n\nThe conversion functions preserve the TimeZone field using unsafe pointer casting (lines 173, 192 in conversion files):\n```go\nout.TimeZone = (*string)(unsafe.Pointer(in.TimeZone))\n```\n\n### Validation Logic\n\n**Primary Validation Functions (pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go):**\n- `ValidateCronJobCreate` (line 757): Validates CronJob on creation, checks metadata name length (max 52 chars), calls validateCronJobSpec\n- `ValidateCronJobUpdate` (line 772): Validates CronJob updates, delegates to validateCronJobSpec\n- `validateCronJobSpec` (line 782): Core validation logic:\n  - Validates schedule format (non-empty required)\n  - Validates TimeZone field via `validateTimeZone` (line 800), only if changed\n  - Validates StartingDeadlineSeconds (non-negative)\n  - Validates ConcurrencyPolicy values\n  - Validates JobTemplate\n  - Validates history limits (non-negative)\n\n**TimeZone Validation (pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go):**\n- `validateTimeZone` (line 859): Comprehensive validation:\n  - Allows nil TimeZone (optional field)\n  - Rejects empty string TimeZone\n  - Validates IANA time zone format (line 870-875): checks for '.', '..', '-' prefix, invalid characters\n  - Rejects 'Local' as invalid (line 877)\n  - Calls `time.LoadLocation()` to validate against system time zone database (line 881)\n  - Uses regex pattern `validTimeZoneCharacters` (line 857) for component validation\n\n**Schedule Format Validation (pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go):**\n- `validateScheduleFormat` (line 833): Validates cron schedule format\n  - Parses schedule with `parsers.ParseCronScheduleWithPanicRecovery`\n  - Enforces mutual exclusivity: cannot use both TimeZone field and TZ/CRON_TZ in schedule (lines 840-843)\n\n### Defaulting Logic\n\n**v1 Defaulting (pkg/apis/batch/v1/defaults.go):**\n- `SetDefaults_CronJob` (line 76): Applied to batch/v1.CronJob\n  - Sets `ConcurrencyPolicy` to `AllowConcurrent` if empty (line 78)\n  - Sets `Suspend` to false if nil (line 81)\n  - Sets `SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit` to 3 if nil (line 84)\n  - Sets `FailedJobsHistoryLimit` to 1 if nil (line 87)\n  - **Note:** TimeZone field has no default (remains nil/empty to use controller's default timezone)\n\n**v1beta1 Defaulting (pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/defaults.go):**\n- `SetDefaults_CronJob` (line 28): Applied to batch/v1beta1.CronJob\n  - Sets `ConcurrencyPolicy` to `AllowConcurrent` if empty (line 30)\n  - Sets `Suspend` to false if nil (line 33, creates new bool)\n  - Sets `SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit` to 3 if nil (line 36, creates new int32)\n  - Sets `FailedJobsHistoryLimit` to 1 if nil (line 40, creates new int32)\n  - **Difference vs v1:** Uses pointer allocation (`new()`) rather than `ptr.To()` helper\n\n### Controller Implementation\n\n**CronJob Controller (pkg/controller/cronjob/cronjob_controllerv2.go):**\n- Uses batch/v1 CronJob via informers and listers\n- Accesses TimeZone field in `syncCronJob` method\n- Validates TimeZone using `time.LoadLocation()` at line 507\n- Creates jobs with timezone annotations\n\n**Utility Functions (pkg/controller/cronjob/utils.go):**\n- `getCronJobTimeZone` (implicit): Extracts TimeZone from CronJob.Spec (line 249)\n- Loads location from TimeZone string or uses UTC as default (line 249)\n- Applies timezone to scheduled time calculations (line 254)\n\n### Registry and Storage\n\n**CronJob Strategy (pkg/registry/batch/cronjob/strategy.go):**\n- `cronJobStrategy`: Implements verification logic for CronJob resources\n- `cronJobStatusStrategy`: Handles status updates separately\n- Uses internal `batch.CronJob` type for storage operations\n\n**Storage (pkg/registry/batch/cronjob/storage/storage.go):**\n- Uses generic registry store with CronJob strategy\n- Handles both spec and status updates\n- Manages CronJob table conversion for kubectl\n\n### Code Generation\n\n**Proto Definitions:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/generated.proto`: Proto definition with TimeZone field (line 79)\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/generated.proto`: Proto definition with TimeZone field (line 79)\n\n**Generated Code:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/generated.pb.go`: Protobuf marshaling/unmarshaling\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/generated.pb.go`: Protobuf marshaling/unmarshaling\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`: Deep copy functions\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`: Deep copy functions\n- `pkg/apis/batch/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`: Internal API deep copy functions\n\n### Client Libraries\n\n**Typed Clients:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/typed/batch/v1/cronjob.go`: v1 CronJob client\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/typed/batch/v1beta1/cronjob.go`: v1beta1 CronJob client\n- Both implement standard CRUD operations\n\n**Fake Clients:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/typed/batch/v1/fake/fake_cronjob.go`\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/typed/batch/v1beta1/fake/fake_cronjob.go`\n\n**Listers and Informers:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/listers/batch/v1/cronjob.go`: Provides indexed access to cached CronJobs\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/informers/batch/v1/cronjob.go`: Shares informer across components\n\n**Apply Configuration:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/applyconfigurations/batch/v1/cronjobspec.go`: Includes TimeZone setter (line 82)\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/applyconfigurations/batch/v1beta1/cronjobspec.go`: Includes TimeZone setter (line 84)\n\n### Migration Path\n\nThe migration from v1beta1 to v1 follows this flow:\n1. External v1beta1 CronJob received by API server\n2. Converted to internal batch.CronJob representation via `Convert_v1beta1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob`\n3. Internal representation used for validation, defaulting, and storage\n4. Internal representation converted back to external v1 CronJob when needed via `Convert_batch_CronJob_To_v1_CronJob`\n5. All conversions preserve the TimeZone field transparently\n6. Validation applied to internal representation ensures consistency across versions\n7. TimeZone field enables timezone-aware cron scheduling without schedule string modification\n\n### Key Differences Between v1beta1 and v1\n\n**Defaulting Strategy:**\n- v1beta1: Uses explicit `new()` allocation for pointer fields\n- v1: Uses `ptr.To()` helper function for consistency\n- Both produce identical default values (ConcurrencyPolicy=Allow, Suspend=false, SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit=3, FailedJobsHistoryLimit=1)\n\n**Field Handling:**\n- TimeZone field is identical in both versions\n- Conversion between versions is transparent and lossless\n- Validation rules are version-agnostic (applied to internal representation)\n"
